Trying a new gym or fitness class can be intimidating. Here’s a few tips to make your experience enjoyable.

1.Bring a friend! 

Taking a friend with you to a new fitness class makes the experience pleasant & holds you accountable.

2.Own your fitness level! 

Our class instructors provide beginner-friendly exercises. We’re here to help! Don’t be afraid to ask for a modification if an exercise is too difficult.

3.Focus on Form

Form focused training is a must at The New You. Take the extra time to perfect your posture, ask the instructor to check that you’re performing each move correctly, and slow down if necessary.

4.Show up early

One of the best ways to feel prepared and ready to conquer a new fitness class is to get there early.

Struggling to find motivation to start?? Here’s a few tips to get you started on your journey! 

✅ Tip 1: Embrace your starting point. 

You’re here now and that’s all that matters. It’s okay to start from where you are, no matter your fitness level. Focus on progress, not perfection.

✅Tip 2: Celebrate your successes

No matter how big or small…Recognize and acknowledge your hard work and achievements, and use them as motivation to keep going.

✅Tip 3: Stay positive and be kind to yourself.

Don’t let negative self-talk or comparison to others bring you down. This is YOUR journey! Remember that every step you take towards your goals is an accomplishment in itself.

Don’t let self-doubt hold you back from achieving your dream life. You deserve this! You are capable of so much more than you think. 

Take that first step towards a healthier, happier you today. 

You got this! 💪❤️

I wanted to learn how to surf so I started the process…😬

I started searching on social media, getting tips and looking for the get good quick cheat code….🤔🤣

I got a board, a wetsuit, I watched the YouTube videos and hit the beach…I couldn’t even stand up…at all!🤦🏾‍♂️ 

After many failed attempts I became frustrated. I blamed the type of board, the wetsuit and the waves…lol

I mean…couldn’t be me 😆 

So I saw some free lessons…I knew it was a sign…..

During the surfing lesson with actual coaches/instructors…I was up for the first time after 3 minutes in the water🙌🏾

Hours of videos, social media searching, even me being in the water myself didn’t really work effectively…😤

By taking ONE lesson I turned hours into minutes 🤯

Let’s dive into these curls—a beloved yet commonly misperformed upper body exercise 😊💪🏾

Here’s some FREE game-changing pointers I share with my clients to ensure they get the most from their workout!🙌🏾

✅ Slow tf down 

✅ Choose a weight you can control (no room for ego lifting here)

✅ No short strokes allowed (full range of motion)

✅ Prevent elbows from rising as the weight ascends ⬆️ 

✅ Maintain a straight and sturdy back (don’t lean back to get it up)

💎 I tell clients to slightly bend their knees to avoid leaning. It works, try it.

✅ Keep those wrists firm, avoiding any bending (grip tight)

✅ Remember to breathe (never hold your breath)

Embrace these principles during your next curl session, and prepare to experience a whole new level of results. 

Share these tips next time you see someone doing curls 💪✨

‼️ Sumo Squats‼️

🙌🏾🙌🏾🙌🏾🙌🏾🙌🏾🙌🏾🙌🏾

Let’s talk about few whys…

⁉️Why the feet wide and toes pointing out⁉️

✅ Target different muscles. Puts more emphasis on the inner thighs, adductors and gluteus medius.

✅ I wanna enhance clients hip mobility. 

⁉️Why do I say chest up ⁉️

✅ So clients don’t cheat and bend their back too far forward without squatting lower. 

✅  Forces core activation…I actually prefer clients to lean over slightly but having the dumbbell down forces them down anyway so it’s a win…

⁉️Why I encourage not locking your knees⁉️

✅ Time under tension (TUT)…engages your muscle fibers for longer periods of time. No rest during the repetition.

Why slow and controlled ⁉️

✅ enhanced muscle building…you wanna grow your 🍑 right?  Slowing down while lowering and rising means longer (TUT), leads to more growth.

Add a few of these tips into your next lower body session and  Feel the difference 💪🏾💪🏾💪🏾😊

In this lighthearted reel, I’m donning the ‘pastor’ hat to share a profound truth - 

Sometimes, the weight we carry isn’t measured in pounds; it’s the emotional baggage that can weigh us down.

And it can weight you down HEAVY!!🥺😩🤦🏾‍♂️

🩹💔We’ve all experienced it, the heaviness that comes from self-doubt, unresolved issues or toxic situationships 🥹

But here’s the sermon, my friends:

1️⃣ Letting Go: Just like shedding physical pounds, releasing emotional weight requires courage. It’s okay to distance yourself from negativity.

2️⃣ Forgiveness: Offering forgiveness, both to others and to yourself, can lighten the load you’ve been carrying.

3️⃣ Self-Care: Prioritize self-love and self-care. Nurture your emotional well-being like you do your physical health.

4️⃣ Seek Support: Don’t be afraid to seek help and lean on your support system. They’re there to help you rise.

🌟 When we release the weight of negativity and pain, we create space for growth, positivity, and personal transformation.

This is all a struggle for me , but I’m learning to do this more and more. Come with me on the journey 💪🏾🙏🏾💯🤎
